  abstract={At present, the field of Chinese named entity recognition mostly introduces external lexicon information to improve the effect of the model. In previous articles, authors mostly use general-purpose lexicon, and their method cannot distinguish the importance of different lexicon information according to the training corpus. In this paper, we propose the approach of dynamic weighting according to the frequency of related words in the corpus when quoting external lexicon. According to recent researches, the long short term memory(LSTM) usually performs better than Transformer in NER task, but it is not suitable for parallel computing. An improved Transformer encoder with a relative position embedding that can better perceive the direction of input sequence is employed in this paper. Experiments demonstrated that the proposed model has better FI measurements than LSTM based models in most instances and significantly saves the training time.},
  keywords={Training;Information science;Computational modeling;Neural networks;Parallel processing;Transformers;Time measurement;Chinese named entity recognition;external lexicon;Transformer;relative position embedding},
